Field_Binary.name: chdo_type
Field_Binary.description: Type attribute of the PN range data CHDO. Set to 10- because this CHDO contains binary data.

Field_Binary.name: chdo_length
Field_Binary.description: Length attribute of the PN range data CHDO value field. Number of bytes after this item. Set to 204.

Field_Binary.name: ul_stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Uplink station calibration value. Values 0.0 to 1.8e5 are allowed; value -1.0 indicates invalid. One range unit (RU) = (exc_scalar_den/exc_scalar_num)/(16*FRQ_UP) where FRQ_UP is the uplink carrier frequency and the two scalars are given in fields 36 and 37. Range is measured in RU to give a stable reference when the uplink is being ramped.

Field_Binary.name: dl_stn_cal
Field_Binary.description: Downlink station calibration value. Values 0.0 to 1.8e5 are allowed; values -1.0 indicates invalid. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: meas_rng
Field_Binary.description: Measured range modulo rng_modulo (field 39). Does not include compensation for station calibration and other adjustments. Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed; value -1.0 indicates invalid. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: rng_obs_dl
Field_Binary.description: Downlink range observable modulo rng_modulo (field 39). Includes measurement adjustments (station calibration, time tag offsets, spacecraft delay, and Z-height). Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed; value -1.0 indicates invalid. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: figure_merit
Field_Binary.description: Probability of Acquistion (formerly called Figure of Merit) -- the probability of acquiring the correct range. Values 0.0 to 100.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: drvid
Field_Binary.description: Differenced Range versus Integrated Doppler (DRVID) measured using Doppler data from carrier. Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: rtlt
Field_Binary.description: Round trip light time (predicted value). Values 0.0 to 86400.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: prn0
Field_Binary.description: Ratio of Ranging power (Pr) to noise power spectral density (N0). Values -10.0 to 90.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: transmit_pwr
Field_Binary.description: Transmitter power. Value 0.0 to 500000.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: invert
Field_Binary.description: Inverted polarity flag. Inverted implies that the polarity of the correlation reference is the invert of what was transmitted. 0 = Not inverted; 1 = Inverted

Field_Binary.name: correl_type
clk_divider
Field_Binary.description: Clock Divider -- the value that ranging reference frequency is divided by to get chip rate. Values 1 to 64 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode1
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #1 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode2
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #2 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode3
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #3 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode4
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #4 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode5
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #5 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

Field_Binary.name: len_subcode6
Field_Binary.description: Subcode #6 length. Values 0 to 64 are allowed; value 0 implies no subcode.

def_subcode1
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #1. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode2
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #2. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode3
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #3. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode4
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #4. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode5
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #5. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: def_subcode6
Field_Binary.description: Definition of Subcode #6. Values 0 to 2**64-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: pn_code_length
Field_Binary.description: PN Code Length -- length of the complete PN pattern (in chips). Values 2 to 2**32-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: transmit_inphs_time
Field_Binary.description: Transmit in-phase time -- offset from time tag of time of zero phase on uplink range signal generation. Values -86400.0 to 86400.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rcv_inphs_time
Field_Binary.description: Receive in-phase time -- offset from time tag of time of zero phase on downlink range signal correlation. Values -86400.0 to 86400.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: carr_sup_rng _modul
Field_Binary.description: Carrier suppression by ranging modulation -- reduction in carrier power due to ranging modulation. Values 0.0 to 15.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_num
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Numerator -- numerator of ratio between ranging reference signal and uplink sky frequency. Values 1 to 2**32-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: exc_scalar_den
Field_Binary.description: Exciter Scalar Denominator -- denominator of ratio between ranging reference signal and uplink sky frequency. Values between 1 and 2**32-1 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_cycle_time
Field_Binary.description: Range cycle time -- integration time for each PN range point. Values 1.0 to 5.0e5 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_modulo
Field_Binary.description: Range measurement modulo (ambiguity) value. Values 0 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: rng_type
fabricated_ul_flag
Field_Binary.description: Fabricated uplink flag -- indicates whether this SFDU was created based on uplink records fabricated in support of 3-way ranging. 0 = SFDU created using uplink records originally generated by UPL and validated by TTC software; 1 = SFDU created using uplink records fabricated by TTC software

Field_Binary.name: rng_noise
Field_Binary.description: Range noise. Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed; value -1.0 indicates invalid. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: rng_obs
Field_Binary.description: Range observable modulko rng_modulo (field 39). Includes all measurement adjustments (station calibration, time tag adjustments, spacecraft delay, and Z-height). Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed; value -1.0 indicates invalid.

Field_Binary.name: rng_dl_prefit_resid_vld_flag
clock_waveform
rng_resid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Range residual tolerance value -- used for setting Range residual tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Applies to rng_dl_prefit_resid (field 61). Not applicable if rng_dl_prefit_resid_vld_flag is 0. Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: drvid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: DRVID tolerance value -- used for setting DRVID tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: prn0_resid_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Pr/N0 residual tolerance value -- used for setting Pr/N0 residual tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Values -10.0 to 90.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_sigma_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Range sigma tolerance value -- used for setting Range sigma tolerance flag. Provided by customer. Values 0.0 to 2**30 are allowed. Not applicable if rng_noise is set to -1.0. For definition of range unit, see field 3.

Field_Binary.name: fom_tol_value
Field_Binary.description: Probability of Acquisition tolerance value (formerly called Figure of Merit). Used in setting of Range Validity flag. Provided by customer. Values 0.0 to 100.0 are allowed.

Field_Binary.name: rng_dl_prefit_resid
Field_Binary.description: Downlink Range Pre-fit Residual (observed range minus predicted range). Values -2**30 to 2**30 are allowed. For definition of range unit, see field 3.
